            <title>[CASSANDRA-9534] Repair data not always saved to system_distributed</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-9534</link>
                <project id="12310865" key="CASSANDRA">Apache Cassandra</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;About 1 out of 5 times, in a ccm-managed cluster, a repair doesn&apos;t write anything to the &lt;tt&gt;system_distributed.parent_repair_history&lt;/tt&gt; table. &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/riptano/cassandra-dtest/blob/master/repair_test.py#L296&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;This dtest&lt;/a&gt; reproduces the error on a 5-node cluster.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
